body_text.text:
Univariate analyses for overall survival and clinical improvement of tocilizumab patients are presented in Tables 3
and 4
. At multivariate analysis, patients with age <75 years had a higher survival (HR 1.46, 1.03 – 2.08, p=0.03, see Figure 3
), whereas patients with baseline PaO2:FiO2 ratio ≥100 showed a slightly higher incidence of clinical improvement at day 28 (HR 1.01, 1.00 – 1.02, p=0.006, see Figure 4
).
